# Delivery and scope

- Work step by step.
- Prioritize MVP simplicity.
- Do not over-engineer.
- Do not add future features unless explicitly requested.
- Do not generate architecture, SQL, frontend and business logic all at once.
- Separate required-for-v1 from optional-for-later.
- Wait for confirmation before moving to the next major step.
- Prefer minimal working code over broad architecture.

## Avoid by default

- RLS
- Advanced auth
- Audit/versioning systems
- Certification workflows
